{
  "page": "King's Justice (title)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg/300px-Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"400\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e7/Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg/450px-Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg 1.5x, /images/e/e7/Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Brittmartin_Ilyn_Payne.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a>, by Brittmartin ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>King's Justice</b> is the royal <a href=\"/index.php/Headsman\" title=\"Headsman\">headsman</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The title takes its name from the legal concept of the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_justice_(concept)\" title=\"King&#39;s justice (concept)\">king's justice</a>, faced by those who break the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_peace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King&#39;s peace\">king's peace</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Duties\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Duties</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Maegor_and_Jaehaerys\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Maegor and Jaehaerys</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#The_Dance_and_Regency\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Dance and Regency</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Recent_History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent History</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Known_King.27s_Justices\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known King's Justices</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Duties\">Duties</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Duties\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The King's Justice is tasked with executing any person sentenced to death by the order of the <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Andals,_the_Rhoynar_and_the_First_Men\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King of the Andals, the Rhoynar and the First Men\">KIng</a> or the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> who speaks with the king's voice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The King's Justice is expected to be fearsome.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The chambers of the King's Justice are located between the ground floor of the Traitor's Walk and the entrance to the dungeons of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Other responsibilities of the King's Justice are managing the dungeons and supervising the <a href=\"/index.php/Chief_gaoler\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chief gaoler\">chief gaoler</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Chief_undergaoler\" title=\"Chief undergaoler\">chief undergaoler</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Undergaoler\" title=\"Undergaoler\">undergaolers</a>, and turnkeys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The King's Justice also supervises the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Confessor\" title=\"Lord Confessor\">Lord Confessor</a>, although that position has not been filled since the days of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Maegor_and_Jaehaerys\">Maegor and Jaehaerys</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Maegor and Jaehaerys\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In the wake of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>'s death and the arrival of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, the King's Justice was arrested and put in the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_cells\" title=\"Black cells\">black cells</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabprince_into_king_-_the_ascension_of_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> After reaching the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_majority\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Age of majority\">age of majority</a> and claiming his rule for himself, King Jaehaerys I replaced the King's Justice, among other lesser offices.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Dance_and_Regency\">The Dance and Regency</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Dance and Regency\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, after Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a> was dismissed as <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> and replaced with Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a>, all the captive <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>— who had once sworn to defend the rights of Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and refused to bend the knee of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>—were dragged one by one before the King's Justice at the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>'s yard. Each man was given one final chance to swear fealty to  Aegon. The King's Justice beheaded Lords <a href=\"/index.php/House_Hayford\" title=\"House Hayford\">Hayford</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Merryweather\" title=\"House Merryweather\">Merryweather</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Harte\" title=\"House Harte\">Harte</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Buckler\" title=\"House Buckler\">Buckler</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Caswell\" title=\"House Caswell\">Caswell</a>, as well as Lady <a href=\"/index.php/House_Fell\" title=\"House Fell\">Fell</a>, eight <a href=\"/index.php/Landed_knight\" title=\"Landed knight\">landed knights</a>, and twoscore servants and retainers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a>, the former <a href=\"/index.php/Grand_Maester\" title=\"Grand Maester\">Grand Maester</a>, was captured in early <a href=\"/index.php/132_AC\" title=\"132 AC\">132&#160;AC</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency of Aegon III</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tyland_Lannister\" title=\"Tyland Lannister\">Tyland Lannister</a>, repeatedly postponed his execution, pointing out that the office of King's Justice remained empty since the end of the Dance.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Tyland's successor, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Unwin_Peake\" title=\"Unwin Peake\">Unwin Peake</a>, appointed Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Victor_Risley\" title=\"Victor Risley\">Victor Risley</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_Risley_Glade\" title=\"Knight of Risley Glade\">Knight of Risley Glade</a>, as the King's Justice in <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On the <a href=\"/index.php/Feast_Day_of_Our_Father_Above\" title=\"Feast Day of Our Father Above\">Feast Day of Our Father Above</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, the gaols and dungeons of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> were emptied, and each prisoner was publicly executed by the King's Justice, with the aid of <a href=\"/index.php/Tessario\" title=\"Tessario\">Tessario</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Fingers_(guards)\" title=\"Fingers (guards)\">Fingers</a>. Among those executed by the King's Justice were a \"<a href=\"/index.php/False_Shepherd\" title=\"False Shepherd\">Shepherd Reborn</a>\", a <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentoshi</a> merchantman accused and found guilty of bringing the <a href=\"/index.php/Winter_Fever\" title=\"Winter Fever\">Winter Fever</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Sisterton\" title=\"Sisterton\">Sisterton</a> to King's Landing, and Orwyle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Victor was arrested in <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, following the confession of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/George_Graceford\" title=\"George Graceford\">George Graceford</a>, which implicated him in the attempt to overthrow power in the <a href=\"/index.php/Secret_siege\" title=\"Secret siege\">secret siege</a> amid the <a href=\"/index.php/Lysene_Spring\" title=\"Lysene Spring\">Lysene Spring</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/136_AC\" title=\"136 AC\">136&#160;AC</a>, Victor was condemned to die, but demanded a <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_battle\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Trial by battle\">trial by battle</a>, in which he was killed by Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gareth_Long\" title=\"Gareth Long\">Gareth Long</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_History\">Recent History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> was appointed as the King's Justice at the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Robert_I_Baratheon_and_Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Wedding of Robert I Baratheon and Cersei Lannister\">wedding of Robert I Baratheon and Cersei Lannister</a>. His appointment was a gift from King <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert</a> to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, the father of his new bride, a sinecure to compensate Ilyn for the tongue he lost while in service to <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> for <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>, sends Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">Beric Dondarrion</a> to hunt down Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a>. According to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Varys\" title=\"Varys\">Varys</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a>, the King's Justice, looked displeased at not having been chosen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> orders Ilyn to execute Eddard at the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG/350px-Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"231\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG/525px-Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG/700px-Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alex_Aparin_The_Price_of_Nobility.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> standing near King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>, by Alex Aparin © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Blackwater\" title=\"Battle of the Blackwater\">Battle of the Blackwater</a>, Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> has Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> remain with her in the Queen's Ballroom of <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor%27s_Holdfast\" title=\"Maegor&#39;s Holdfast\">Maegor's Holdfast</a> in the Red Keep,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok57.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> in order to kill Cersei and her captive, <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a>, should the Red Keep fall to <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> When <a href=\"/index.php/Osfryd_Kettleblack\" title=\"Osfryd Kettleblack\">Osfryd Kettleblack</a> informs Cersei that a groom and two maidservants where caught trying to flee the Red Keep with three of the king's horses, she has the King's Justice execute them and place their heads on pikes outside the stables.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the throne room following the battle, Joffrey orders Ilyn to behead a defiant <a href=\"/index.php/House_Florent\" title=\"House Florent\">Florent</a> bastard who refuses to renounce <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Light\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord of Light\">Lord of Light</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a> demands the services of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> from Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> as his condition for leading the expedition to <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Cersei acquiesces as she blames the King's Justice for the the escape of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> from the dungeons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>, Cersei Lannister suggests that she will have to appoint a new King's Justice due to Ser Ilyn's absence, in order to execute <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>, whom Cersei hopes to charge with treason.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Known_King's_Justices\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_King.27s_Justices\">Known King's Justices</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known King&#039;s Justices\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Victor_Risley\" title=\"Victor Risley\">Victor Risley</a>, during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, from <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> until <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a>, during the reigns of <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_I_Baratheon\" title=\"Robert I Baratheon\">Robert I Baratheon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen I Baratheon</a>.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>If the wicked do not fear the King's Justice, you have put the wrong man in the office.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>From the shadows at the back of the hall, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ilyn_Payne\" title=\"Ilyn Payne\">Ilyn Payne</a> appeared. The specter at <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">the feast</a>, thought Tyrion as he watched the King's Justice stride forward, gaunt and grim.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos60.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_Justice_(title)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_